revision.text:
{{DISPLAYTITLE:Scroll_Texture_Model}}
{{Special|222|lineid, scrollbits|Scrolling|Texture, Model|use=line}}

{{warning|text=This special is not fully supported by the [[UDMF]] map format.  Certain parameters, noted below, have been made obsolete by the ability to directly specify properties within the linedef structure.  These parameters should be set to 0 when using the UDMF format.}}

* ''lineid'': The ID of the line to be affected. ''Obsolete in UDMF.''
* ''scrollbits'': The type of scroller:
** bit 0(1): Displacement scroller
** bit 1(2): Accelerative scroller

== Examples ==
{{noexamples}}

== Conversions from linedef types ==
The following Doom map format types can be converted as :
{| {{prettytable}}
!Type!!Conversion!!Trigger
|-
|{{icon|Boom}} 218:Accel Tagged Wall w.r.t 1st Side's Sector || Scroll_Texture_Model (lineid, 2) || 
|-
|{{icon|Boom}} 249:Scroll Tagged Wall w.r.t 1st Side's Sector || Scroll_Texture_Model (lineid, 1) || 
|-
|{{icon|Boom}} 254:Scroll Tagged Wall, Same as Floor/Ceiling || Scroll_Texture_Model (lineid, 0) || 
|}
